# 🧠 Deepfake Detection System (Multi-Model + Explainable AI)

## 🚀 Live Demo  
- https://huggingface.co/spaces/Aryan19461/Deepfake_Detection_Model

---

## 📌 Overview  

This project is a **Deepfake Detection Web Application** that identifies whether an image is **Real or Fake** using deep learning models.  

The system is designed not only for prediction but also for **interpretability**, allowing users to understand *why* a model classified an image as fake.

It combines **multiple CNN-based architectures** with **Grad-CAM visualization** to highlight manipulated regions in images.

---

## 🎯 Objectives  

- Detect deepfake images with high accuracy  
- Support multiple deep learning models  
- Provide **real-time predictions via web interface**  
- Improve transparency using **Explainable AI (Grad-CAM)**  
- Enable easy deployment using **Hugging Face Spaces**

---

## 🏗️ System Architecture  

The system follows this pipeline:


User Input (Image/Webcam)
↓
Preprocessing (Resize + Normalization + Face Crop)
↓
Model Selection (CNN / MobileNetV3 / Xception)
↓
Prediction (Real / Fake + Confidence)
↓
Grad-CAM Visualization
↓
Final Output + Explanation



---

## 🤖 Models Used  

### 1. Simple CNN  
- Lightweight baseline model  
- Fast inference  
- Helps in comparison with advanced models  

### 2. MobileNetV3  
- Optimized for **real-time performance**  
- Suitable for low-resource environments  
- Balanced speed and accuracy  

### 3. XceptionNet  
- High-performance deep learning model  
- Uses **depthwise separable convolutions**  
- Best accuracy among all models  

